pmetzger@snark.shearson.com (Perry E. Metzger) writes:

>People forget that governments are not trustworthy. Here in the US we
>are spoiled -- we have had a stable and fairly free regime for over
>two centuries. However, this is rare. Most of the world has had
>revolutions upheavals at frequent intervals. Wouldn't it be a shame if
>we set up our system so as to assure that a dictatorial regime could
>be successful? Consider that with the capacity to easily and
>conveniently monitor all communications and with the population
>effectively disarmed for the first time in US history we would have
>already put into place the infrastructure for a lasting tyranny.

Yes isn't it sad how the poor disarmed citizens of England, France,
Germany, Italy, Canada, etc are under the tyrannous thumb of
dictatorship.
